    <h2>Design Guidelines</h2>
    <p class="sg_subtle">
      1. Properties should be defined on element as specifically as possible <br>
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Define table cell widths ON the cell<br>
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Inline styling is best<br>
      2. Use an email pre-flighter to ensure CSS is declared inline <br>
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- <a href="http://premailer.dialect.ca/" target="_blank">Premailer</a><br>
      3. Avoid .png's.<br>
      4. Avoid floats.<br>
      5. Tables are good! Use them for layout.<br>
      6. Avoid whitespace in table cells.<br>
      7. Be as specific/explicit in declarations as possible. Avoid shorthand.<br>
      8. Some email clients ignore link color declarations. Use spans inside your anchor tags.<br>
      <br>
      <a href="http://www.emaildirect.com/blog/2013/06/breaking-some-email-design-best-practices/" target="_blank">List of email clients feature support (6/2013)</a>
